dct_description_sm: par Guillaume De L'Isle Geographe de L'Academie Royale de la Sciences.
Shows the region of Swabia, one of the Imperial Circles of the Holy Roman Empire.
Originally published in France in 1704; this map was published as part of an atlas in Amsterdam 1742, with a similar edition 1745.
Appears in L'Isle’s Atlas nouveau, contenant toutes les parties su Monde, ou sont exactement remarquees les empires, monarchies, royaumes, etats, republiques, Amsterdam: Covens et Mortier, 1742.
dct_publisher_sm: chez I. Cóvens et C. Mortier, geographes,
